to Cartagena.

253
00:28:47,809 --> 00:28:49,550
Cartagena?

254
00:28:49,811 --> 00:28:52,348
Angel, you are hell
and gone from Cartagena.

255
00:28:52,606 --> 00:28:54,347
Cartagena's over there
on the coast.

256
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:57,521
- But they told me this bus-
- Who told you that?

257
00:28:57,778 --> 00:29:01,191
- That man that... That nice man
who pulled a gun on you. Uh-huh.

258
00:29:02,491 --> 00:29:04,482
What else did he tell you?

259
00:29:06,161 --> 00:29:09,574
- Please, I need your help.
- That's my new career, huh?

260
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:12,072
- It's very-
- Lady-Lady...

261
00:29:12,334 --> 00:29:15,577
half a year's work just flew south
for the winter, all right?

262
00:29:15,837 --> 00:29:17,828
My jeep is totaled.

263
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:19,731
In five minutes,
everything I own in the

264
00:29:19,755 --> 00:29:21,583
world's gonna be wet,
so can you lighten up?

265
00:29:21,843 --> 00:29:25,677
- I really don't have the time.
- I'll pay you.

266
00:29:25,931 --> 00:29:29,077
You don't understand. It's a matter of life
and death. If I don't get to my sis-

267
00:29:29,101 --> 00:29:33,060
- How much?
- Fifty dollars?

268
00:29:35,107 --> 00:29:37,018
Oh, shit.

269
00:29:37,276 --> 00:29:39,267
Well, you said you just lost
everything you owned.

270
00:29:39,528 --> 00:29:43,647
- Not my sense of humor.
- Well, I'll pay you a hundred dollars.

271
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:46,148
Two hundred dollars!

272
00:29:52,749 --> 00:29:57,414
I'll do it...
for five.

273
00:29:57,671 --> 00:30:02,541
What?
I'll pay you $250.

274
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:06,510
Now, I ain't cheap...

275
00:30:06,763 --> 00:30:09,596
but I can be had.

276
00:30:09,850 --> 00:30:14,515
My minimum price for taking a stranded
woman to a telephone is $400.

277
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:19,557
- Will you take 375 in traveler's checks?
- American Express?

278
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:22,105
- Of course.
- You got a deal.

279
00:30:22,362 --> 00:30:24,103
Good.

280
00:30:58,106 --> 00:30:59,938
Señor Zolo.

281
00:31:01,693 --> 00:31:04,685
Assemble your men!

282
00:31:27,594 --> 00:31:29,585
Ow!

283
00:31:39,940 --> 00:31:42,056
You got any valuables
in that suitcase?

284
00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:45,605
No. Yes!
All my clothes and things.

285
00:31:45,862 --> 00:31:49,776
- You got an umbrella?
- No.

286
00:31:50,033 --> 00:31:53,992
- You got a good pair of walking shoes?
- They're all like these.

287
00:31:54,246 --> 00:31:56,078
Uh-huh.

288
00:32:09,302 --> 00:32:13,387
- Okay, let's make some time.
- You b-

289
00:32:16,685 --> 00:32:18,642
Aw, shit!

290
00:33:04,065 --> 00:33:06,227
Oh, goddamn it!
What a ride, huh?

291
00:33:06,485 --> 00:33:08,226
Whoo!

292
00:33:08,487 --> 00:33:11,821
I'm telling you, this is turning out to be
one hell of a morning!

293
00:33:12,073 --> 00:33:14,030
Ah!

294
00:33:14,284 --> 00:33:16,946
You okay?

295
00:33:17,204 --> 00:33:19,320
I said, are you hurt?
What's the matter?

296
00:33:19,581 --> 00:33:21,913
Are you paralyzed from the neck up?
Are you hurt?

297
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:24,033
- No.
- Good.

298
00:33:25,295 --> 00:33:28,128
- What's your name?
- Uh-Uh-

299
00:33:28,381 --> 00:33:31,294
I'm J-Joan Wilder.

300
00:33:31,551 --> 00:33:35,294
Joan Wilder,
welcome to Colombia!

301
00:33:43,563 --> 00:33:46,055
Hi. Hi.

302
00:33:46,316 --> 00:33:48,648
Oh, hi, Ma.
It's me, Irving.

303
00:33:48,902 --> 00:33:50,643
Ralph, you little twerp,
where are you?

304
00:33:50,904 --> 00:33:53,020
Calm down, Ma.
Who says I never call?

305
00:33:53,281 --> 00:33:55,067
Will you for Christ's sake
tell me the story?

306
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:57,441
All right, cousin.
As usual, you got us...

307
00:33:57,702 --> 00:33:59,443
in some serious shit here.

308
00:33:59,704 --> 00:34:02,617
First of all, the stupid dame
got on the wrong bus.

309
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:08,210
Now I'm stuck in some kind
of spico military compound.

310
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:11,546
They're mobilizing
for Iwo Jima here.

311
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,882
- Do they know who you are?
- Oh-Oh-

312
00:34:14,135 --> 00:34:16,593
What do you think, I'm going up
and introducing myself...

313
00:34:16,846 --> 00:34:19,508
to every cop in the pueblo?

314
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:22,428
And another
little tidbit, cousin.

315
00:34:22,686 --> 00:34:25,849
- Guess who else is here.
- Zolo.

316
00:34:26,106 --> 00:34:28,894
Oh! Oh, well,
give the man a cigar.

317
00:34:29,150 --> 00:34:32,484
You're goddamned right, Zolo!
He got in my car.

318
00:34:32,737 --> 00:34:34,853
Not only are we kidnappers,
but I'm about to have...

319
00:34:35,115 --> 00:34:37,402
a close encounter
with a cattle prod.

320
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:40,026
- Has he got his boys with him?
- No, no, no.

321
00:34:40,287 --> 00:34:42,198
He's making do
with the local yo-yos.

322
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:46,782
Oh, no. Oh!

323
00:34:47,043 --> 00:34:48,909
- Look-
- Goddamn it, Ralph!

324
00:34:49,170 --> 00:34:51,707
- Get that map!
- Don't yell at me, Ira!

325
00:34:51,965 --> 00:34:54,377
Don't yell at me.
Look, you want to kill me?

326
00:34:54,634 --> 00:34:56,375
Take me back to Queens
and kill me.

327
00:34:56,636 --> 00:34:59,674
Don't let me die in a jungle
like a goddamned snake.

328
00:34:59,931 --> 00:35:02,218
Ralph, goddamn it!
I don't care what you gotta do.

329
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:05,058
Just get me that map!

330
00:35:08,607 --> 00:35:11,816
Little sister
took the wrong road.

331
00:35:12,068 --> 00:35:15,106
And that third party
I told you about...

332
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:17,149
he's tagging along.

333
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:19,193
The man who killed my husband?

334
00:35:19,451 --> 00:35:22,159
The butcher
who killed your husband.

335
00:35:22,412 --> 00:35:26,155
A very powerful man with
his own private army to back him up.

336
00:35:26,416 --> 00:35:30,410
And whether he calls himself Dr. Zolo,
Minister of Antiquities...

337
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:34,459
or Colonel Zolo, Deputy Commander
of the Secret Police...

338
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:37,128
he's still just a butcher.

339
00:35:41,264 --> 00:35:44,256
Look at those snappers, will ya?

340
00:35:56,946 --> 00:35:58,857
What's the matter?
You sick?

341
00:35:59,115 --> 00:36:01,777
Uh, no.
I lost my button.

342
00:36:02,035 --> 00:36:04,948
- You lost what?
- I lost my button.

343
00:36:05,205 --> 00:36:06,946
My button.

344
00:36:07,207 --> 00:36:09,949
You"re gonna lose
a lot more than that.

345
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:29,267
- These were Italian.
- Now they're practical.

346
00:36:29,521 --> 00:36:31,603
Is nothing that I own
sacred to you?

347
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:35,353
Only your $375.

348
00:36:41,116 --> 00:36:43,858
Cops!

349
00:36:44,119 --> 00:36:47,202
What the hell do they want?

350
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:49,617
I haven't done anything lately.

351
00:36:57,465 --> 00:36:59,547
I'm shooting at a cop.

352
00:37:01,761 --> 00:37:05,550
- Wait a minute. He's after you.
- Wha-

353
00:37:05,807 --> 00:37:09,766
- Who the hell are you??
- Well, I'm-I'm a romance novelist.

354
00:37:10,019 --> 00:37:13,102
You're what?

355
00:37:13,356 --> 00:37:15,313
- What are you doing here?
- I told you.

356
00:37:15,567 --> 00:37:18,559
- My sister's life depends on me.
- Don't give me that shit.

357
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:20,780
I thought you were donating
a kidney or something.

358
00:37:22,657 --> 00:37:24,694
Christ, here they come.

359
00:37:24,951 --> 00:37:27,943
This may be a good time
to try on those shoes right about now.

360
00:37:35,170 --> 00:37:38,003
- Wait!
- Deal's off, lady.

361
00:37:39,132 --> 00:37:41,123
Wait!

362
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:49,382
Lady, you are bad news.

363
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:57,514
What'd you do,
wake up this morning and say...

364
00:37:57,776 --> 00:38:00,393
“Today I'm gonna ruin
a man's life”?

365
00:38:12,832 --> 00:38:16,826
- Do you know where you're going?
- Looks like some kind of trail.

366
00:38:17,086 --> 00:38:19,293
This is a trail?

367
00:38:33,812 --> 00:38:35,928
Lady, you are a jinx!

368
00:38:37,273 --> 00:38:39,731
Well, what about the bridge?

369
00:38:39,984 --> 00:38:43,727
That ain't a bridge.
Goddamn pre-Colombian art.

370
00:38:43,988 --> 00:38:46,025
You can't get across that.

371
00:38:48,117 --> 00:38:50,700
Aw, shit.

372
00:38:50,954 --> 00:38:52,786
All right, all right.

373
00:38:53,039 --> 00:38:56,577
We're gonna hold 'em off right from here.
You just stay right behind me.

374
00:38:58,545 --> 00:39:01,754
Goddamn it! I knew I should've
listened to my mother.

375
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:26,023
I could've been
a cosmetic surgeon.

376
00:39:26,281 --> 00:39:28,739
Five hundred thou a year,
up to my neck in tits and ass.

377
00:39:42,589 --> 00:39:44,546
Lady, I hope
you're taking notes...

378
00:39:44,799 --> 00:39:48,667
'cause you got a real live
death scene going on right here.

379
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:01,596
Romantic novelist, my ass.

380
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:41,060
Holy shit!

381
00:41:16,349 --> 00:41:18,841
Joan!

382
00:41:37,036 --> 00:41:39,903
What the hell are you doing?

383
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:43,657
Drinking? I could've been killed,
and you're drinking!

384
00:41:48,715 --> 00:41:50,080
Wait!

385
00:41:51,884 --> 00:41:54,091
- ¡Vamos!
- ¡Vamos!

386
00:42:14,782 --> 00:42:16,773
Are we stopping?

387
00:42:27,128 --> 00:42:29,119
Be my guest.

388
00:43:27,188 --> 00:43:29,179
You okay?

389
00:43:39,200 --> 00:43:41,191
Come on.

390
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:05,973
- Is anybody else in there?
- No.

391
00:44:06,227 --> 00:44:08,719
No, it's a cargo plane.

392
00:44:10,273 --> 00:44:12,640
What is all this?

393
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:15,733
All this? About five to life
in the States...

394
00:44:15,987 --> 00:44:17,728
a couple of centuries down here.

395
00:44:17,989 --> 00:44:19,980
Oh, marijuana.

396
00:44:20,241 --> 00:44:22,073
Oh, you smoke it.

397
00:44:23,161 --> 00:44:27,246
- I went to college.
- Yeah, sure.

398
00:45:04,493 --> 00:45:06,985
- All right! Okay.
- Oh!

399
00:45:10,499 --> 00:45:13,491
Oh, God, do I love
those flyboys.

400
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:33,978
What?

401
00:45:35,483 --> 00:45:37,815
This is Elaine's favorite drink.

402
00:45:47,787 --> 00:45:50,620
You gonna tell me about
that sister of yours?

403
00:45:53,251 --> 00:45:55,367
I already did.

404
00:46:00,758 --> 00:46:03,921
Her husband died, and-

405
00:46:04,178 --> 00:46:06,510
and I've come down here
to comfort her.

406
00:46:09,225 --> 00:46:12,388
- Uh-huh.
- It's the truth.

407
00:46:18,192 --> 00:46:20,684
Right. Yeah,
it's the truth.

408
00:46:25,032 --> 00:46:27,148
All right.
I'm gonna make a fire.

409
00:46:32,331 --> 00:46:35,540
You got any dry matches in here?

410
00:46:39,547 --> 00:46:41,538
Well, lookie here.

411
00:46:43,092 --> 00:46:46,005
Uh-Oh, no, don't!

412
00:46:51,058 --> 00:46:53,220
I think you and I
oughta have a talk.

413
00:46:56,063 --> 00:46:58,054
All right.

414
00:47:07,283 --> 00:47:09,866
Yeah, that's what I call
a campfire.

415
00:47:13,080 --> 00:47:15,697
Whoo!

416
00:47:19,253 --> 00:47:23,793
So they're ransoming
your sister for this El Corazon.

417
00:47:24,050 --> 00:47:26,792
That's Spanish for “The Heart.”

418
00:47:28,763 --> 00:47:30,970
This map here
leads to The Heart.

419
00:47:33,309 --> 00:47:35,300
But the heart of what?

420
00:47:35,561 --> 00:47:38,269
I don't care.

421
00:47:42,943 --> 00:47:45,685
You see here where it says
this El Corazon is hidden...

422
00:47:45,946 --> 00:47:47,857
in Cordoba province?

423
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:48,808
Mm-hmm.

424
00:47:48,832 --> 00:47:50,982
So we're sitting
right in the middle of it.

425
00:47:51,243 --> 00:47:56,079
All I care about is my sister,
and that map is her life.

426
00:47:56,332 --> 00:48:00,701
Like hell it is. Whatever's at the end
of this map is your sister's life.

427
00:48:00,961 --> 00:48:04,704
Now, we get our hands
on this El Corazon...

428
00:48:04,965 --> 00:48:07,127
then you got something
to bargain with.

429
00:48:08,636 --> 00:48:12,174
- I knew it would happen.
- You knew what would happen?

430
00:48:12,431 --> 00:48:14,217
All you care about
is yourself, isn't it?

431
00:48:14,475 --> 00:48:16,555
I knew that from the first moment
I laid eyes on you.

432
00:48:16,769 --> 00:48:19,511
( Oh, is that the first moment
when I saved your ass? I Chuckles )

433
00:48:19,772 --> 00:48:21,513
There. You see?
There you go.

434
00:48:21,774 --> 00:48:25,142
You have no finesse, no style.

435
00:48:25,403 --> 00:48:29,442
A real man doesn't have to-
to draw attention to his actions.

436
00:48:29,698 --> 00:48:33,441
You're-You're just-
You're a mondo-dizmo.

437
00:48:33,702 --> 00:48:37,286
I'm-What am I? I'm what?

438
00:48:37,540 --> 00:48:40,703
You're a man who takes money
from stranded women.

439
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:44,328
A real man, he's honest...

440
00:48:44,588 --> 00:48:47,706
and forthright and trustworthy.

441
00:48:49,635 --> 00:48:55,130
Would you please do me the courtesy of
looking at me when I'm speaking to you?

442
00:48:55,391 --> 00:48:58,304
I mean, this is exactly
what I'm talking about.

443
00:48:58,561 --> 00:49:00,848
I mean, if you had any
kind of manners-If you-

444
00:49:26,589 --> 00:49:28,500
Goddamn bushmaster.

445
00:49:28,757 --> 00:49:31,465
Is it, uh, poisonous?

446
00:49:31,719 --> 00:49:35,257
Yeah, but very tasty.

447
00:49:38,267 --> 00:49:40,258
Uh-oh.

448
00:50:12,301 --> 00:50:15,589
Uniforme.

449
00:50:20,601 --> 00:50:24,435
See, you gotta figure
sulphur-crested cockatoos...

450
00:50:24,688 --> 00:50:28,306
they go for about 800 a shot.

451
00:50:28,567 --> 00:50:30,399
Then you got gentle red-tails.

452
00:50:30,653 --> 00:50:33,270
They're-They're close
to 2,000 each.

453
00:50:34,740 --> 00:50:39,735
Shit, I figure I lost close to
15,000 bucks in that bus crash.

454
00:50:39,995 --> 00:50:42,453
- Wow!
- Mm-hmm.

455
00:50:43,541 --> 00:50:45,623
You wanna know something crazy?

456
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:48,868
- What?
- I don't even know your name.

457
00:50:49,129 --> 00:50:50,961
Well, you never asked me.

458
00:50:54,552 --> 00:50:57,385
Excuse me.
I'd really like to know-

459
00:50:57,638 --> 00:51:01,552
Colton.
Jack T. Colton.

460
00:51:01,809 --> 00:51:04,301
- What does the “T” stand for?
- Aw, goddamn it, man!

461
00:51:04,562 --> 00:51:07,395
The Doobie Brothers broke up.
Shit!

462
00:51:07,648 --> 00:51:10,640
- When did that happen?
- How long have you been down here?

463
00:51:10,901 --> 00:51:13,233
Aw, man!

464
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:17,355
- Forever. I don't know.
- Were you always into birds?

465
00:51:17,616 --> 00:51:21,735
Mm-mm. No, no.
I, uh-

466
00:51:21,996 --> 00:51:24,533
No, I was, uh-

467
00:51:24,790 --> 00:51:26,531
I was into shortcuts.

468
00:51:28,002 --> 00:51:30,585
Birds just seemed to be
a fast way to get what I wanted.

469
00:51:30,838 --> 00:51:34,172
And a hell of a lot healthier
than dealing in this crap.

470
00:51:35,342 --> 00:51:37,674
What is it you want?

471
00:51:41,932 --> 00:51:43,969
I think I'm gonna throw
another key on the fire.

472
00:51:44,226 --> 00:51:46,684
No, please.
I'm getting dizzy.

473
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:52,940
What do you want, seriously?

474
00:51:53,193 --> 00:51:55,525
I'd really like to know.

475
00:51:59,992 --> 00:52:04,782
I came down here on a coffee boat
about a year and a half ago, right?

476
00:52:05,039 --> 00:52:07,371
Christ, what a job that was.

477
00:52:09,043 --> 00:52:12,206
But I couldn't get over
that ocean though, you know?

478
00:52:13,297 --> 00:52:17,165
Yeah, I love the ocean.

479
00:52:17,426 --> 00:52:22,592
You know, you just
gotta get out there all by yourself.

480
00:52:22,848 --> 00:52:25,180
Nobody else around.

481
00:52:25,434 --> 00:52:27,266
It's beautiful.

482
00:52:29,521 --> 00:52:31,683
So that's what I want.

483
00:52:31,940 --> 00:52:34,272
Try to get enough money together,
buy a boat...

484
00:52:34,526 --> 00:52:37,484
sail around the world.

485
00:52:37,738 --> 00:52:41,402
So you're just gonna
sail away all by yourself?

486
00:52:43,911 --> 00:52:46,528
Yeah.

487
00:52:46,789 --> 00:52:49,531
Sounds lonely, Jack T. Colton.

488
00:53:01,762 --> 00:53:05,972
Well, what does
the “T” stand for?

489
00:53:09,311 --> 00:53:11,473
Trustworthy.

490
00:53:22,366 --> 00:53:24,357
Mmm.

491
00:53:27,746 --> 00:53:32,035
Aw, man, I tell ya,
one hell of a morning.

492
00:53:32,292 --> 00:53:35,000
It's turned into
a bitch of a day.

493
00:53:55,983 --> 00:53:58,224
“Tenedor dell Diablo.”

494
00:54:01,989 --> 00:54:04,481
The Devil's Fork.

495
00:54:28,849 --> 00:54:30,806
Zolo.

496
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:58,083
- Friendly, aren't they?
- Drug runners.

497
00:54:59,171 --> 00:55:01,208
Just try to look mean.

498
00:55:01,465 --> 00:55:03,297
Buenos Dias.

499
00:55:08,388 --> 00:55:10,299
- Oh, shit.
- What's the matter?

500
00:55:10,557 --> 00:55:12,764
Nothing.

501
00:55:22,236 --> 00:55:24,273
Hey, hombre.

502
00:55:26,406 --> 00:55:29,023
Hey, hombre!

503
00:55:36,375 --> 00:55:38,366
- Okay, here we go.
- What?

504
00:55:38,627 --> 00:55:40,600
I just knew I should've
listened to my mother.

505
00:55:40,624 --> 00:55:41,624
Hey, hombre.

506
00:55:43,590 --> 00:55:45,922
You ready?

507
00:55:46,176 --> 00:55:49,714
Uh, excuse me.

508
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:52,430
Gentlemen,
we are in need of a car.

509
00:55:56,687 --> 00:55:59,770
Can any of you lovely gentlemen
tell me where-

510
00:56:01,525 --> 00:56:05,393
Only one car in village.
Juan, the bell maker.

511
00:56:06,947 --> 00:56:08,938
The bell maker.

512
00:56:10,325 --> 00:56:12,316
Thank you.

513
00:56:17,291 --> 00:56:19,202
Bell maker, my ass.

514
00:56:19,459 --> 00:56:22,542
That fuselage we slept in is probably
one of old Juan's lost shipments.

515
00:56:22,796 --> 00:56:24,537
- You mean he's a drug de-
- Shh!

516
00:56:24,798 --> 00:56:27,711
- Just don't say the word out loud, okay?
- Dope?

517
00:56:27,968 --> 00:56:29,800
Come on.
Let's go.

518
00:56:45,485 --> 00:56:48,193
All right.
Now, you-you hold back.

519
00:56:48,447 --> 00:56:50,279
This one I'll handle.

520
00:57:06,256 --> 00:57:07,997
What do you want, gringo?

521
00:57:08,258 --> 00:57:10,545
Oh, you speak English.
Oh, that's-that's great.

522
00:57:10,802 --> 00:57:12,588
We understand that
you have a car.

523
00:57:12,846 --> 00:57:14,928
We would like
to rent it or buy it.

524
00:57:15,182 --> 00:57:16,968
We have to get to a town.

525
00:57:17,225 --> 00:57:20,593
What do you call this
I'm livin' in, a pigsty?

526
00:57:20,854 --> 00:57:23,687
Uh, no. No, no.
This is lovely. It's-

527
00:57:23,941 --> 00:57:27,309
- Hit the road.
- No, amigo, you don't understand-

528
00:57:27,569 --> 00:57:30,527
- Hit the road.
- Senor, I'd-

529
00:57:33,116 --> 00:57:36,609
Vaya con Dios, gringo.

530
00:57:36,870 --> 00:57:38,986
It's cool.
It's cool.

531
00:57:39,247 --> 00:57:41,705
It's... no problem.

532
00:57:41,959 --> 00:57:44,041
Vaya con Dios.

533
00:57:46,088 --> 00:57:48,045
Oh.

534
00:57:50,425 --> 00:57:53,089
Okay, Joan Wilder,
write us out of this one.

535
00:57:53,113 --> 00:57:54,113
Joan Wilder?

536
00:57:56,014 --> 00:57:59,723
Joan Wilder?
The Joan Wilder?

537
00:58:02,771 --> 00:58:04,978
You are Joan Wilder,
the novelist?

538
00:58:05,232 --> 00:58:06,973
Yes, I am.

539
00:58:07,234 --> 00:58:09,817
I read your books.
I read all your books.

540
00:58:10,070 --> 00:58:11,070
Come In.

541
00:58:11,279 --> 00:58:14,988
The one who writes
the books I read to you on Saturdays.

542
00:58:15,242 --> 00:58:17,700
Juanita.

543
00:58:17,953 --> 00:58:19,990
Juanita.
Es Juanita.

544
00:58:20,247 --> 00:58:23,160
- Come in.
- Adios, Amiga.

545
00:58:23,417 --> 00:58:25,875
I can't believe you're here.
Joan Wilder.

546
00:58:26,128 --> 00:58:27,869
Oh.

547
00:58:28,130 --> 00:58:30,167
I've been reading your books
all these years.

548
00:58:30,424 --> 00:58:32,961
I'm so honored to have you here.
I can't believe it.

549
00:58:33,218 --> 00:58:34,959
Welcome to my humble house.

550
00:58:35,220 --> 00:58:38,087
Joan Wilder!

551
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:40,464
Oh, I-I'm sorry.
I haven't introduced myself.

552
00:58:40,726 --> 00:58:42,558
I'm Juan.
I live here.

553
00:58:42,811 --> 00:58:45,303
¿Qué Paso?

554
00:58:45,564 --> 00:58:48,397
The greatest novelist.
Get the door, please.

555
00:59:22,642 --> 00:59:24,553
Buenos Dias.

556
00:59:24,811 --> 00:59:26,552
¿Gringos?

557
00:59:26,813 --> 00:59:28,554
¿Americanos?

558
00:59:28,815 --> 00:59:31,147
- ;Gringos?
- No.

559
00:59:31,401 --> 00:59:33,142
- ¿Americanos?
- No.

560
00:59:44,206 --> 00:59:47,415
Come In.
Make yourself at home.

561
00:59:47,667 --> 00:59:49,578
- Ever read The Return of Angelina?
- No.

562
00:59:49,836 --> 00:59:52,578
That woman makes me hungry.

563
00:59:52,839 --> 00:59:54,625
How about Love's Wicked Kiss?

564
00:59:54,883 --> 00:59:56,624
No, I haven't read
that one either.

565
00:59:56,885 --> 00:59:58,626
Read it. Take it.
I have many copies.

566
00:59:58,887 --> 01:00:02,881
I have here The Ravagers, and I am
waiting for Angelina's Savage Secret.

567
01:00:03,141 --> 01:00:05,223
I am so glad you're
here in Colombia.

568
01:00:05,477 --> 01:00:08,139
I want to show you all
around my beautiful village.

569
01:00:08,396 --> 01:00:13,186
We have colorful tile roofs, typical
cobblestone streets and very rich fields.

570
01:00:13,443 --> 01:00:16,105
I was born here
and so was my whole family.

571
01:00:16,363 --> 01:00:18,424
What I would really
like would be a phone.

572
01:00:18,448 --> 01:00:19,606
No, no, no. No phones.

573
01:00:19,866 --> 01:00:21,903
I hate phones.
I don't have a phone.

574
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:25,778
But have a drink.
Let's hang out. Look.

575
01:00:26,039 --> 01:00:28,576
Like it? I can be in one of your books.

576
01:00:28,834 --> 01:00:32,748
Oh, your drink.
I got Southern Comfort.

577
01:00:33,004 --> 01:00:36,247
Or Michelob, Kirin,
Becks, Dos Equis...

578
01:00:36,508 --> 01:00:39,250
Perrier, Anchor Steam,
Dr. Brown-

579
01:00:39,511 --> 01:00:42,549
- How about a Xerox machine?
- Yes, but she is broken.

580
01:00:47,686 --> 01:00:49,973
Where is the nearest phone?

581
01:00:50,230 --> 01:00:53,643
- Many miles from here.
- Can we get there in your car?

582
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:56,688
- Who told you I had a car?
- The men in the village.

583
01:00:56,945 --> 01:00:59,437
They told you I had a car?

584
01:00:59,698 --> 01:01:03,236
They're such comedians.
They meant my little mule Pepe.

585
01:01:14,921 --> 01:01:17,583
Not bad for a little mule, eh?

586
01:01:21,094 --> 01:01:23,631
Now Pepe's warming up.

587
01:01:27,559 --> 01:01:31,223
- What are we stopping for?
- I can't hurt my favorite pig.

588
01:01:45,285 --> 01:01:47,071
Look out!
Watch it!

589
01:01:52,292 --> 01:01:55,250
I - Oh!

590
01:01:55,503 --> 01:01:59,041
See over there by the fence?
That's where my mother was born.

591
01:01:59,299 --> 01:02:02,917
And see that tree? The third tree up
the ridge? My brother planted that tree.

592
01:02:10,310 --> 01:02:12,847
Okay, Pepe, let's lose 'em.

593
01:02:14,773 --> 01:02:16,639
Whoa!

594
01:02:17,984 --> 01:02:21,522
Whoa!

595
01:02:21,780 --> 01:02:24,317
- This guy's crazier than I am.
- Gracias. Yeah!

596
01:02:51,059 --> 01:02:53,426
What the hell you doin'?
That field was cover.

597
01:02:53,687 --> 01:02:55,519
I wanted to show you
this other field.

598
01:02:58,024 --> 01:03:00,356
Oh, shit!

599
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:03,693
This guy who's following you,
he's very persistent.

600
01:03:21,965 --> 01:03:25,208
No problem.
My Little Mule is fireproof.

601
01:03:30,724 --> 01:03:33,432
- See that river?
- What, the one without the bridge?

602
01:03:35,937 --> 01:03:38,099
This river is the main water
supply for many villages.

603
01:03:38,356 --> 01:03:40,514
What do you mean, “the
one without the bridge”?

604
01:03:40,538 --> 01:03:42,065
It feed's right into the Amazon.

605
01:03:42,319 --> 01:03:45,277
The one without the bridge.
Where the hell are you going?

606
01:03:45,530 --> 01:03:48,898
Lupe's Escape.
I've used it many times in the past.

607
01:04:10,096 --> 01:04:13,430
Whoo!

608
01:04:20,899 --> 01:04:24,108
Whoo-hoo!

609
01:04:29,699 --> 01:04:32,031
You're okay now.

610
01:04:32,285 --> 01:04:34,401
You need Little Mule
to use Lupe's Escape.

611
01:04:34,662 --> 01:04:39,407
You know, that river is impossible to cross
for 200 miles in either direction.

612
01:04:39,667 --> 01:04:44,127
In fact over that mountain
the river becomes wild.

613
01:04:44,381 --> 01:04:48,670
Muy peligroso.
Waterfalls, rapids.

614
01:04:49,761 --> 01:04:52,253
Angelina country.
Right, Joan?

615
01:04:52,514 --> 01:04:54,881
- Whatever happened to Lupe?
- Oh, ay, ay, ay.

616
01:04:55,141 --> 01:04:58,884
- Terrible disappointment to family.
- / can imagine.

617
01:04:59,145 --> 01:05:02,228
He entered the priesthood,
so I took over the business.

618
01:05:02,482 --> 01:05:04,564
It's for the best.
I'm not so reckless.

619
01:05:04,818 --> 01:05:07,776
He might have ended up hanging from
El Tenedor Del Diablo there.

620
01:05:08,029 --> 01:05:10,987
- It used to happen to barndidos.
- “El Tenedor dell Diablo”?

621
01:05:13,785 --> 01:05:17,779
Okay. Hey, let's hit it. We're on a roll.

622
01:05:18,039 --> 01:05:20,576
I'm sorry I cannot take you
all the way to Cartagena.

623
01:05:20,834 --> 01:05:22,620
Beyond this town
I am a wanted man.

624
01:05:22,877 --> 01:05:25,369
But in the morning
there is always a bus.

625
01:05:25,630 --> 01:05:27,462
It will take you.

626
01:05:34,931 --> 01:05:35,170
Of all the things
you can say to me right now...

627
01:05:35,432 --> 01:05:38,220
Of all the things
you can say to me right now...

628
01:05:38,476 --> 01:05:43,266
“I've lost her”, Ralph, is gonna get
the most teeth broken in your mouth.

629
01:05:43,523 --> 01:05:45,804
Look, bullet head, if they're hiking
through the jungle...

630
01:05:45,859 --> 01:05:47,691
there's nothin'
I can do about it.

631
01:05:47,944 --> 01:05:50,185
I have a car.
I am not Tarzan.

632
01:05:50,447 --> 01:05:55,817
I have been through every one-horse
shithole for a 200-mile radius.

633
01:05:56,077 --> 01:05:58,865
You should have seen the river
I had to traverse this morning.

634
01:05:59,122 --> 01:06:01,955
So don't give me any of
your crap, you gutless wonder.

635
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:05,917
You have been an embarrassment to me and
the whole family ever since you were born.

636
01:06:06,171 --> 01:06:07,912
And one more thing, Ira-

637
01:06:08,173 --> 01:06:10,460
- Joan.
- Yeah?

638
01:06:10,717 --> 01:06:14,711
You are the luckiest son of a bitch that
walked the face of the earth. She's here.

639
01:06:14,971 --> 01:06:19,681
- She's there?
- She's right here.

640
01:06:19,934 --> 01:06:23,302
She's coming right
toward the phone booth.

641
01:06:23,563 --> 01:06:25,520
She's with some guy.

642
01:06:25,773 --> 01:06:27,764
How do I know?
She likes guys.

643
01:06:28,026 --> 01:06:29,858
So do you, maricón.

644
01:06:43,291 --> 01:06:45,123
Yeah, all the rooms have baths.

645
01:06:45,376 --> 01:06:48,164
Oh, that's-that's great.
You speak English too.

646
01:06:48,421 --> 01:06:50,708
That's great.

647
01:06:50,965 --> 01:06:54,833
Listen, you wouldn't have a Xerox machine
around here, would you?

648
01:06:55,094 --> 01:06:56,926
Yeah.
We have one in the back.

649
01:06:58,848 --> 01:07:02,216
I mean, it's big enough
to take, like, uh, map size?

650
01:07:02,477 --> 01:07:04,309
Yeah. Complete.

651
01:07:05,313 --> 01:07:08,305
Yes, I understand.
I'll do that.

652
01:07:12,278 --> 01:07:14,394
Well, I talked to Blaine.
She's all right.

653
01:07:14,656 --> 01:07:16,896
They're gonna wait for me
to take the bus in the morning.

654
01:07:17,116 --> 01:07:19,089
That's great. Then
slide, man. You're covered.

655
01:07:19,113 --> 01:07:19,778
I don't know.

656
01:07:20,036 --> 01:07:22,778
- He sounded so smug.
- Who?

657
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:24,905
- That bastard that's got Elaine.
- Sure he is.

658
01:07:25,166 --> 01:07:27,486
You're bringing what he wants.
You're bringing him the map.

659
01:07:27,710 --> 01:07:29,542
Yeah.

660
01:07:32,423 --> 01:07:36,132
Well, I guess this is it.

661
01:07:38,346 --> 01:07:40,303
Uh, yeah, I guess so.

662
01:07:41,349 --> 01:07:43,306
Oh.

663
01:07:44,310 --> 01:07:46,642
375.
That was the contract, right?

664
01:07:46,896 --> 01:07:48,728
Yeah. That was it.

665
01:07:56,197 --> 01:07:58,438
The least I can do
is buy you some dinner.

666
01:07:58,700 --> 01:08:00,562
Looks like it's gonna
be a hell of a party.

667
01:08:00,586 --> 01:08:01,586
I'd like that.

668
01:08:02,745 --> 01:08:05,237
Tell you what.
Uh, I got a room in the hotel.

669
01:08:05,498 --> 01:08:08,490
Why don't you go get cleaned up?
I'll buy us some new rags.

670
01:08:08,751 --> 01:08:12,210
- Number seven.
- Seven? That's my lucky number.

671
01:08:13,798 --> 01:08:15,709
Mine too.

672
01:08:52,712 --> 01:08:54,669
It's just beautiful.

673
01:08:55,840 --> 01:08:57,831
Thank you, jack.

674
01:09:14,067 --> 01:09:17,310
I think your writing's hot. It's great.

675
01:09:17,570 --> 01:09:20,187
I mean it. I'm tellin' you.
I'm impressed. I am.

676
01:09:20,448 --> 01:09:22,189
You've never even read the book.

677
01:09:22,450 --> 01:09:25,192
I know.
I know.

678
01:09:25,453 --> 01:09:27,285
I suppose...

679
01:09:28,665 --> 01:09:31,828
it's my way of living
in another age.

680
01:09:32,085 --> 01:09:34,622
If you did that,
I never would have met you.

681
01:09:36,297 --> 01:09:38,584
I got you something.

682
01:09:47,517 --> 01:09:49,599
El Corazon?

683
01:10:17,588 --> 01:10:21,126
- Let's dance.
- Oh, no. I can't.

684
01:10:21,384 --> 01:10:23,000
- Come on. I'll show you.
- I-No.

685
01:10:23,261 --> 01:10:25,002
- No.
- Try. Trust me.

686
01:10:34,856 --> 01:10:36,847
Jo'

687
01:11:10,391 --> 01:11:12,302
I- I lost my langostino.

688
01:11:23,112 --> 01:11:25,649
No, no, no, no! Wait!
No, no! Wait!

689
01:11:25,907 --> 01:11:27,739
Calm down, lady!

690
01:11:29,660 --> 01:11:31,697
Jo'

691
01:11:53,976 --> 01:11:55,887
Señora.

692
01:12:47,738 --> 01:12:53,575
Someday, if I had the money,
I'd take you...

693
01:12:53,828 --> 01:12:56,570
I'd sail away.

694
01:12:56,831 --> 01:12:59,448
Just the two of us.

695
01:12:59,709 --> 01:13:01,541
Around the world and back again.

696
01:13:05,298 --> 01:13:08,336
I promise you.
I promise you we'd do that.

697
01:13:17,351 --> 01:13:20,059
Why haven't you taken
the map away from me?

698
01:13:23,900 --> 01:13:26,892
What are you talking about?

699
01:13:27,153 --> 01:13:30,896
I saw that tree today,
the Devil's Fork that's on the map.

700
01:13:31,157 --> 01:13:32,898
You know how close we are?

701
01:13:33,159 --> 01:13:36,242
Well, sure I do, but what has that
got to do with it?

702
01:13:36,495 --> 01:13:40,079
I was thinking about something you said,
about having more to bargain with.

703
01:13:40,333 --> 01:13:43,416
Yeah. Yeah, the best way to help your
sister is to get that treasure.

704
01:13:43,669 --> 01:13:46,832
Then you could waltz into Cartagena.
You're holding all the cards.

705
01:13:48,883 --> 01:13:50,999
I'd love to see you
on that boat.

706
01:13:53,554 --> 01:13:56,967
But, Jack, if we have to give it
up to save Elaine-

707
01:13:57,224 --> 01:13:59,013
Then we give it
up. I mean, it's your

708
01:13:59,037 --> 01:14:01,183
sister. Hell, yeah. Of
course we give it up.

709
01:14:01,437 --> 01:14:04,555
But that's the point.
At least we've got the leverage to do it.

710
01:14:10,112 --> 01:14:12,103
Okay.

711
01:14:13,699 --> 01:14:15,610
Okay.

712
01:14:15,868 --> 01:14:17,700
Let's go for it.

713
01:15:03,541 --> 01:15:05,532
Shh!
Shh, shh, shh, shh!

714
01:15:10,089 --> 01:15:11,875
He just won't quit.

715
01:15:28,065 --> 01:15:30,432
- What are you doing?
- I'm hot-wiring the car.

716
01:15:31,485 --> 01:15:33,567
Try the key.

717
01:16:01,140 --> 01:16:04,599
- There it is. That's the shrine.
- Yep.

718
01:16:04,852 --> 01:16:06,638
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

719
01:16:36,092 --> 01:16:38,459
Well, this-this can't be all.

720
01:16:38,719 --> 01:16:40,551
There's gotta be
another clue here.

721
01:16:40,805 --> 01:16:43,092
Well, landmarks change,
things grow.

722
01:16:43,349 --> 01:16:45,431
All that stuff, you know?

723
01:16:45,684 --> 01:16:49,678
Oh. Hey, you hear that?

724
01:16:51,190 --> 01:16:53,101
Waterfall.

725
01:16:53,359 --> 01:16:55,191
Look, Jack.

726
01:16:57,029 --> 01:16:58,940
All right, Joan!

727
01:17:17,049 --> 01:17:19,006
Whoo!

728
01:17:20,553 --> 01:17:22,760
- You all right?
- Yeah.

729
01:17:25,850 --> 01:17:28,968
Whoa!
This has got to be it.

730
01:17:30,521 --> 01:17:33,058
Hey, what-

731
01:17:33,315 --> 01:17:37,024
what does
“Leche de la Madre” mean?

732
01:17:37,278 --> 01:17:39,019
Leche de la Madre?

733
01:17:39,280 --> 01:17:41,112
Yeah. It's on the map.

734
01:17:42,658 --> 01:17:44,774
It means “mother's milk”.

735
01:17:45,035 --> 01:17:46,867
- Mother's milk?
- Yeah.

736
01:18:02,344 --> 01:18:04,255
I'll be goddamned,

737
01:18:05,556 --> 01:18:07,763
Mama, I'm home.

738
01:18:14,148 --> 01:18:16,765
- I can't believe I'm doing this.
- What?

739
01:18:17,026 --> 01:18:20,519
Digging for treasure...
with you.

740
01:18:22,865 --> 01:18:24,902
Jack?

741
01:18:25,159 --> 01:18:27,491
Yeah?

742
01:18:27,745 --> 01:18:29,611
You're the best time
I've ever had.

743
01:18:33,667 --> 01:18:35,658
I never been anybody's
best time before.

744
01:19:11,830 --> 01:19:14,663
It's a priceless statue.

745
01:19:19,713 --> 01:19:22,751
Somebody out there's got
a really sick sense of humor.

746
01:19:23,008 --> 01:19:24,749
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

747
01:19:25,010 --> 01:19:27,172
My first book,
Treasures of Lust..

748
01:19:27,429 --> 01:19:29,170
I hid the treasure
inside the statue.

749
01:19:42,945 --> 01:19:45,528
Oh.

750
01:19:52,955 --> 01:19:54,992
Jesus Christ,
we're in a lot of trouble.

751
01:19:57,376 --> 01:19:59,208
Understatement of the year,
asshole.

752
01:20:01,880 --> 01:20:04,463
Is there anybody
who isn't following you?

753
01:20:06,051 --> 01:20:09,009
Put the goods in the bag.
Come on.

754
01:20:13,726 --> 01:20:15,717
Now move it,
before Batman comes home.

755
01:20:15,978 --> 01:20:19,016
It's time I had a chauffeur,
Miss Wilder.

756
01:20:20,316 --> 01:20:22,523
Back off me, creep!
Just back off!

757
01:20:22,776 --> 01:20:25,859
Oh. Oh, I'm the creep, huh?
Well, at least I'm honest.

758
01:20:26,113 --> 01:20:29,777
I'm stealin' this stone. I'm not tryin'
to romance it out from under her.

759
01:20:30,034 --> 01:20:33,823
Wait a minute now.
Going for the stone was my idea.

760
01:20:34,079 --> 01:20:37,993
Aw, that's what all the good
con artists want you to think.

761
01:20:38,250 --> 01:20:41,914
He made you think you needed it,
you sap. Get in and drive.

762
01:20:42,171 --> 01:20:44,162
Come on. Move it.
Move it.

763
01:20:47,343 --> 01:20:49,254
Move it!

764
01:20:49,511 --> 01:20:52,253
See how you like being stuck in-

765
01:20:52,514 --> 01:20:54,676
Holy shit!

766
01:20:55,851 --> 01:20:58,263
Oh! Get in!

767
01:21:03,650 --> 01:21:06,108
- Which way do we go?
- Follow that stone!

768
01:21:23,504 --> 01:21:25,791
Mounties!

769
01:21:35,474 --> 01:21:37,465
Hit it!

770
01:21:59,123 --> 01:22:02,366
- Where the hell you goin'?
- Where am I goin'?

771
01:22:03,502 --> 01:22:05,493
How about Lupe's Escape?

772
01:22:05,754 --> 01:22:07,961
Whoa!

773
01:22:26,442 --> 01:22:28,809
Where you goin'? Quit steering.
You're not going anywhere.

774
01:22:34,783 --> 01:22:36,694
Oh, no!

775
01:22:40,038 --> 01:22:43,747
- What are we gonna do now?
- Jump!

776
01:23:15,908 --> 01:23:20,368
Hey!
Joan Wilder, hey!

777
01:23:20,621 --> 01:23:22,612
What a comeback!

778
01:23:22,873 --> 01:23:24,910
Yeah.

779
01:23:25,167 --> 01:23:27,249
Man, I thought you drowned.

780
01:23:27,503 --> 01:23:29,335
I did.

781
01:23:30,339 --> 01:23:33,548
- You okay?
- Oh, sure.

782
01:23:33,800 --> 01:23:36,383
I'm great.
I'm fine.

783
01:23:36,637 --> 01:23:38,469
Only you're on that side.

784
01:23:38,722 --> 01:23:41,089
There's no way
across this sucker.

785
01:23:41,350 --> 01:23:43,091
You did this on purpose!

786
01:23:43,352 --> 01:23:46,344
What the hell are you talkin' about?
We just went over a waterfall!

787
01:23:46,605 --> 01:23:48,937
Admit it!
You planned this all along.

788
01:23:49,191 --> 01:23:51,478
I knew I couldn't depend on you.
I knew it!

789
01:23:55,989 --> 01:23:58,230
What's the name of
that hotel in Cartagena?

790
01:23:58,492 --> 01:24:01,405
Hotel Cartagena.
What do you care?

791
01:24:01,662 --> 01:24:06,327
All right. Now, you just head towards
the sunset, and you'll make it.

792
01:24:06,583 --> 01:24:09,200
- And I'll be there.
- Oh, yeah, sure.

793
01:24:09,461 --> 01:24:12,624
With El Corazon in your pocket.
What about my sister?

794
01:24:12,881 --> 01:24:17,296
Well, they don't have to know about this.
You got the map.

795
01:24:17,553 --> 01:24:20,261
- Well, you've got the stone.
- Yeah.

796
01:24:26,103 --> 01:24:29,471
- I'll meet you there! Trust me!
- What?

797
01:25:10,439 --> 01:25:12,430
So you made it finally.

798
01:25:14,484 --> 01:25:15,365
Got the map?

799
01:25:15,389 --> 01:25:18,102
Yes. I brought it. I
want to talk to Elaine.

800
01:25:18,363 --> 01:25:21,901
No, you can't talk to her
till I get it.

801
01:25:22,159 --> 01:25:24,070
All right.
Now look out your window.

802
01:25:25,287 --> 01:25:29,030
- See the fort across the bay? The tower?
- Yes.

803
01:25:29,291 --> 01:25:32,784
You take a water taxi
right outside your hotel.

804
01:25:33,045 --> 01:25:38,131
You meet me there
in two hours, all by yourself.

805
01:25:55,692 --> 01:25:58,935
- Hello?
- Has Jack Colton checked in?

806
01:25:59,196 --> 01:26:01,062
In the last two minutes, no.

807
01:27:21,778 --> 01:27:23,769
Over here.

808
01:27:34,916 --> 01:27:37,283
Stop right there.

809
01:27:37,544 --> 01:27:39,751
Let me see the map.

810
01:27:40,005 --> 01:27:43,339
- Where are you?
- Let me see the map.

811
01:27:44,634 --> 01:27:49,219
- Let me see Elaine.
- Joanie?

812
01:28:00,025 --> 01:28:02,608
Drop the map and back off.

813
01:28:11,995 --> 01:28:14,532
If this isn't genuine-

814
01:28:17,250 --> 01:28:19,958
If you've pulled a fast one-

815
01:28:37,229 --> 01:28:39,345
Joan Wilder...

816
01:28:39,606 --> 01:28:42,815
you and your sister...

817
01:28:44,152 --> 01:28:46,109
can go!

818
01:28:50,992 --> 01:28:52,903
Hey.

819
01:28:53,161 --> 01:28:55,243
It's okay.
It's all right.

820
01:29:05,715 --> 01:29:07,581
I missed you at the hotel.

821
01:29:12,973 --> 01:29:14,964
We all did.

822
01:29:24,693 --> 01:29:27,606
You brainless broad.
You let him follow you here.

823
01:29:34,286 --> 01:29:38,496
This map is nothing.
They already have the stone.

824
01:29:43,962 --> 01:29:46,875
I had it in my hands, Ira.

825
01:29:47,132 --> 01:29:51,592
These hands that are gonna
break every bone in your body.

826
01:29:54,639 --> 01:29:56,596
Later.

827
01:30:08,612 --> 01:30:12,697
- Where is it?
- I don't know.

828
01:30:14,200 --> 01:30:17,943
- Where is the stone?
- I don't-

829
01:30:21,958 --> 01:30:24,495
We dug. We didn't find anything.

830
01:30:56,952 --> 01:30:59,865
Crocodiles shed tears
when they eat their prey.

831
01:31:00,121 --> 01:31:02,158
You have heard of these tears,
I am sure.

832
01:31:02,415 --> 01:31:05,407
But have you seen them?

833
01:31:05,669 --> 01:31:07,751
Stop it!

834
01:31:26,106 --> 01:31:28,939
Look at those snappers.

835
01:31:31,569 --> 01:31:35,938
You can fore-go this agony.
Simply tell me, where is El Corazon?

836
01:31:36,199 --> 01:31:38,440
Where is The Heart?

837
01:31:38,702 --> 01:31:42,411
- Where is the stone?
- All right! Just let her go, will you?

838
01:31:42,664 --> 01:31:45,076
She doesn't know where it is.
I've got it.

839
01:31:45,333 --> 01:31:48,291
Where is it?

840
01:31:51,047 --> 01:31:53,960
- It's in a safe place.
- Where is it?

841
01:31:58,847 --> 01:32:00,963
Where is it?

842
01:32:42,557 --> 01:32:44,969
Choke on it.

843
01:32:54,944 --> 01:32:57,231
Thank you.

844
01:33:10,335 --> 01:33:12,246
Get down!

845
01:33:28,019 --> 01:33:29,976
All right, honey, come on.

846
01:33:53,044 --> 01:33:55,001
Hurry! Hurry!

847
01:33:58,049 --> 01:34:02,259
Guys! Muchachos!
Bring the boat around!

848
01:34:02,512 --> 01:34:06,722
Hold them down!
Let me get to the boat!

849
01:34:43,136 --> 01:34:45,176
- Just a little more. Come on.
- Where are we going?

850
01:34:52,353 --> 01:34:55,766
¡Muchachos!
¡Ándale!

851
01:35:01,070 --> 01:35:04,313
Vámonos!

852
01:35:04,574 --> 01:35:07,282
Ira!
Ira!

853
01:35:08,578 --> 01:35:11,991
- Come back here, Ira!
- Jump, Ralph! Jump!

854
01:35:12,248 --> 01:35:13,989
I can't swim.
You know that, Ira.

855
01:35:14,250 --> 01:35:15,991
I'll come back for you.

856
01:35:16,252 --> 01:35:19,119
- You promise?
- I'll send the boat back for you, Ralph!

857
01:35:19,380 --> 01:35:21,792
- When?
- Soon!

858
01:35:22,050 --> 01:35:25,338
- How soon?
- Very soon!

859
01:35:30,433 --> 01:35:32,765
No. No.

860
01:35:33,019 --> 01:35:34,885
No!

861
01:35:39,025 --> 01:35:41,062
Where do you think
you're going, old pal?

862
01:35:41,319 --> 01:35:43,185
Come on.
Cough it up.

863
01:35:43,446 --> 01:35:45,983
Wait!
Wait!

864
01:35:51,454 --> 01:35:53,445
Joanie?

865
01:35:55,750 --> 01:35:58,583
How will you die, Joan Wilder?

866
01:35:58,836 --> 01:36:02,500
Slow like a snail?

867
01:36:03,508 --> 01:36:06,125
Or fast like a shooting star?

868
01:36:40,878 --> 01:36:43,745
'Jack!
»

869
01:36:44,007 --> 01:36:45,998
Jack!

870
01:36:51,222 --> 01:36:53,213
Jack!

871
01:36:59,564 --> 01:37:02,773
Come on, you bastard. Give me a break.

872
01:37:06,696 --> 01:37:09,063
Jack!

873
01:37:10,742 --> 01:37:12,574
Damn it!

874
01:38:30,988 --> 01:38:32,979
Jack.

875
01:38:35,785 --> 01:38:37,776
It's okay.
It's okay.

876
01:38:38,037 --> 01:38:39,698
Come on back, Ira!
Ira!

877
01:38:39,956 --> 01:38:41,804
You're my cousin, Ira!
Don't you remember?

878
01:38:41,828 --> 01:38:42,493
I'll be back!

879
01:38:42,750 --> 01:38:45,833
Your mother, my mother!

880
01:38:46,879 --> 01:38:50,042
That way! That way!
He's gettin' away!

881
01:38:50,299 --> 01:38:52,916
- He's got it all! Go that way!
- Let's get outta here!

882
01:38:53,177 --> 01:38:54,918
- Joanie?
- Yeah?

883
01:38:55,179 --> 01:38:56,920
Okay. All right.
Here's what we gotta do.

884
01:38:57,181 --> 01:38:59,581
Get to the American consulate.
Just-Just tell 'em everything.

885
01:38:59,725 --> 01:39:00,557
Where are you going?

886
01:39:00,581 --> 01:39:02,605
They might even believe
you. But just one thing:

887
01:39:02,687 --> 01:39:06,430
Don't mention my name.
Cartagena cops and I go way back.

888
01:39:06,691 --> 01:39:11,185
- Elaine, it's been a pleasure.
- You're leaving? You're leaving me?

889
01:39:24,208 --> 01:39:27,576
You're gonna be all right,
Joan Wilder.

890
01:39:27,837 --> 01:39:29,578
Yeah.

891
01:39:45,563 --> 01:39:47,554
You always were.

892
01:39:56,866 --> 01:39:58,857
Jack Colton!

893
01:40:06,209 --> 01:40:08,200
Damn.

894
01:40:30,942 --> 01:40:34,355
Well, that is far and away
your best book.

895
01:40:34,612 --> 01:40:37,354
I can't believe how fast
you cranked this out.

896
01:40:37,615 --> 01:40:38,786
So you really like it?

897
01:40:38,810 --> 01:40:41,199
Like it? Look at me.
Look at me. I'm a mess.

898
01:40:41,452 --> 01:40:44,410
It made me cry. Don't tell anybody,
or I'll cut your heart out.

899
01:40:44,664 --> 01:40:47,873
I love the end where he dives off
the high wall and swims away.

900
01:40:48,125 --> 01:40:52,710
And then he meets her at the airport.
They sail off around the world together.

901
01:40:52,964 --> 01:40:56,002
God, I can't believe
how this got to me.

902
01:40:56,259 --> 01:40:59,718
Well, I was, uh, inspired.

903
01:40:59,971 --> 01:41:04,260
Joanie, you are now
a world-class hopeless romantic.

904
01:41:04,517 --> 01:41:06,975
No. Hopeful.

905
01:41:11,691 --> 01:41:13,523
Hopeful romantic.

906
01:41:16,445 --> 01:41:18,903
- Hey, lady.
- Hey, pretty lady.

907
01:41:19,156 --> 01:41:22,490
- No, thanks. Nope.
- Come on. Name brand. Name brand.

908
01:41:22,743 --> 01:41:24,825
Never wear 'em.

909
01:41:25,079 --> 01:41:26,540
This will look great
with what you're

910
01:41:26,564 --> 01:41:28,322
wearin' right now.
Five dollars, it's yours.

911
01:41:48,144 --> 01:41:50,636
Hey!

912
01:42:12,043 --> 01:42:13,954
I like your boots.

913
01:42:14,211 --> 01:42:18,830
Yep. That poor old yellow-tailed guy
developed a fatal case of indigestion.

914
01:42:19,091 --> 01:42:20,877
Died right in my arms.

915
01:42:21,886 --> 01:42:24,298
I can't blame him.
If I were to die...

916
01:42:24,555 --> 01:42:26,341
there's nowhere else
on earth I'd rather be.

917
01:42:26,599 --> 01:42:29,182
I couldn't stop
thinking about you.

918
01:42:29,435 --> 01:42:31,267
I even read one of your books.

919
01:42:32,521 --> 01:42:35,479
- Then you know how they all end.
- Yeah.

920
01:42:35,733 --> 01:42:37,565
- Hi.
- Hi.